<br>
There are a couple of reasons for this.  <br>
<br>
First, pets seem to follow their own set of rules, they aren't exactly mobs, but they aren't exactly players either.  Somehow, low level pets are quite capable of dealing damage to higher level mobs.  My guild killed the remains-spawned Venril Sathir the other day, and I logged &amp; parsed the fight.  My level 42(54 summon) water pet came in 3rd after a 60 shadownknight(HT disc) and a level 54 rogue with epic.  He outdamaged 53 and 54 shissar'd monks and a 52 shissar'd ranger with epics.  That mob was level 55.<br>
<br>
Second, for Rak'Ashiir the pets being used are fire pets.  They cast a very powerful damage shield(about 35-40pts) on themselves, and I would imagine that a huge portion of the damage comes from that damage shield.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Mages really don't get many DD spells post 50. Am I missing something? <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well, sirocco at 55 is a great spell for mages.  Not useful all the time, but I've been able to realize ~2.8-2.9 damage/mana effeciency using it, which is better than the cap on lava bolt, our next most effecient nuke at 55.  The hard numbers for laval bolt are 2.7, and after resists and missed bolts it is likely to be even lower.<br>
<br>
57 is Shock of Steel, which isn't an impressive nuke by wizzie standards, but it is a large upgrade to  the 49 nuke.  It's <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> a bolt, and it has an interrupt(not stun) component.  There is also the new shock of fiery blades from luclin which I really don't know much about yet.<br>
<br>
When we aren't fighting I make mod rods.  Sometimes I coth, sometimes I don't.  I think I cothed the puller 3-4 times in the Umbral Plains last night(it was our first time there).  Today he only needed it once I think.<br>
